name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text: cold showers, a trashed lobby and unreliable package delivery are all things you can look forward to at the standard. packages are left out in the open for anyone to take, maintenance never comes and staff is consistently unavailable. broken (and extremely loud) appliances in a 8 week old apartment building, fire alarms when you turn on the heat, you name it. not to mention advertised amenities are just straight up not here (tesla, lower level retail). very disappointed in my experience for the very high price i am paying. i have tried to talk to staff and they’re never available!* would not recommend.
owner_answer: Thank you for your feedback Tatiana, I am sorry to see you are so disappointed with our community. Our electric car has arrived and is active, and the lower retail is complete and awaiting a tenant. Our offices are open during the week from 10am-6pm, on Saturday from 10am-5pm and on Sunday 12pm-5pm, we don't have any missed calls from you from our system, but feel free to stop by the office at any time during our business hours and we would be happy to assist you.

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text: I was in a major bind to get out of my lease due to company relocation and the leasing manager Jordan was an incredible help with finding a lease takeover. Apartment itself was the perfect studio for the year I was out here.
owner_answer: Jordyn, thank you so much for the positive feedback! We wish you all the best on your next step in life.

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text: From my experience visiting people here, it was absolutely awful. Between the several times I visited, countless problems occurred. The gym, lobby, and study rooms were completely trashed from flooding that occurred because the staff kept the temperature too low. The gym was out of service both times I visited which was 2 months apart. On top of this, the power in most of the rooms barely worked. The outlets didn't function which prevented any charger or lights to work with the exception of the one overhead light. Clearly, the building was built horribly. From my understanding, utility bills were several hundred dollars per person per month which is the most outrageous expense I've ever heard. Next, the hot tub/pool was "out of service" pretty much the entire year. There was no explanation for why it was unusable and remained untouched and unfixed until pretty much the last week of classes. The structural elements of this place were ridiculous. For being a newly built apartment building, this place looked like a trashed several decade old build. Walls were cracking and separating from the floor. Also, from the burst pipes I previously mentioned, several tenants' rooms were completely destroyed. From the individuals I talked to, it sounded like they were promised to have their rooms fixed within a couple months. As it turns out, the horrible management failed to have any desire to follow through. Ultimately, these individuals never got to return to their apartments. These ruined parts of the building were essentially a construction site the entire year. Loud fans tried to air out the smell of mildew and paint. Cardboard and dust covered the floors and walls. I'm so glad I wasn't one of the tenants here. I was staying with friends for what added up to be maybe 3 weeks. Those 3 weeks enlightened me to just had bad a residence and a management team can be. The workers were unresponsive and rude. They pretended everything was fine with the apartment while things were clearly in disrepair. From what I heard and saw, maintenance orders went unanswered and unresolved for months. It's insane how much they charge for this place. I would never live here.
owner_answer: Hey Jacob, we apologize when you have visited the property it has been a less than pleasurable visit. I would encourage your friend who is a resident to reach out to our staff to address any of their concerns further. Here is our contact information info@thestandardannarbor.com, (734) 391.6980.

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text: The Standard being right in the middle of downtown AA but still walkable to campus is so ideal. But honestly the staff is what really makes this place. They're literally always on call and handle everything with decorum while looking at things from a personal point of view. I feel safe here!
owner_answer: Thank you for your positive feedback Bushra. You have been a pleasure to have in our community this year!

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text:
Last year I was at The One. I thought that was the worst apartment ever. But now, with The Standard, I'll say The One is even a great choice.
JUST NEVER CONSIDER THIS APARTMENT.
owner_answer: Thank you for your review. We would like to learn more about the issues you are having. Please contact our leasing office to set up an appointment with a member of our staff so we can work toward a resolution. Thanks!

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text: Poor communication. Fees are hidden. It’s a 11 month lease contract paid over 12 months. Still waiting to get clarification on the parking fees. Very troubling.
owner_answer: Shalini, thank you for taking the time to leave a review.  We are sorry to hear about your poor experience.  Please contact the office staff if things are still not addressed.

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text: I am the father of a former Michigan student. My daughter, transferred from Michigan in September. It is now March. Over 6 months the Standard team did absolutely NOTHING to find someone to take over her lease. We paid 6 months of rent and utilities for an empty room and still they want us to pay another 6 months to be released from our use lease. Their service has been absolutely HORRIBLE; like I said they did ABSOLUTELY nothing to help us find someone. They have been happy to just cash checks in exchange for providing ZERO service or effort.I can do nothing but recommend that no one even consider renting here unless it is an absolute last resort. Do not expect ANY service other than a check cashing service. I have never been less impressed with a “professional” organization.
owner_answer: Hi Patrick! I am so sorry to hear about you and your daughter's situation. Our agreements offer a no-cause termination clause and lease re-assignment options that are offered in situations like these. We would be happy to help connect any future residents to those looking to re-assign their lease however, we can not guarantee interest and encourage our residents to advertise their unique space on different platforms. I'll email you a link with further details on our policy, recommendations to help you re-assign your lease, and different options for you to contact our team while we work together in this process. ~Beverly C., Associate Community Manager

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text: The Standard apartments are a complete and utter disaster. The only thing that staff can stay on top of here is kicking people out of the gym. The pool deck and big TV are deceiving, because the TV is never on and the grills down there do not work. The only thing that is good about this place is the gym, which is now closed because they are waiting on a third party to make some "repairs". Every question or concern seems to be blamed on a third party. The lobby is always filled with trash and smells awful. The showers have been cold more than hot, and our balcony door has been broken for four months. This caused problems with cold air coming in spiking our electric bill $100 over the average. The rent is also way overpriced. I was thinking about renewing, but then they raised the prices for next year. If you want to be taken advantage of, sign with The Standard. One positive is there has been one staff member who seems to follow up with us the most. This place has been underwhelming.
owner_answer:
Luke, 

We apologize that your experience has been anything but excellent. I would love to sit down and discuss some of these areas of improvement if you have some time. Please reach out to us at the leasing office to discuss further if you find some time in the near future.


Aaron 
Standard Ann Arbor

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text: After doing a "tour" of a model unit last winter, my roommates and I were ecstatic to be living at The Standard this year. However, our perception quickly shifted upon moving in. Constant maintenance issues that take weeks to be resolved, promised amenities that either don't exist or are unavailable, and messy common areas have led to a less than ideal living experience. We have had ongoing maintenance issues in our apartment that have been left unattended for months. Our attempts to reach the leasing office lead to vague answers that don't resolve issues. For the high price that this building charges, it has not seemed worth it after one semester. I suggest looking elsewhere for housing, as you will not get your money's worth here.
owner_answer:
Hi Joshua,
We are sorry to see you've had a bad experience with our community! It is our goal to provide the best living experience possible for our residents. If you have any additional feedback regarding your experience you would like to share, or if there is anything we can do to assist with any concerns you might have, please feel free to contact at info@thestandardannarbor.com as we would be happy to assist you.
Best,
Standard Team

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text: The building is magnificent and the staff is very friendly and helpful. The huge gym, pool deck, and clubhouse access are all features you don’t get at other places. The best part about The Standard is that the customer service is top notch!
owner_answer: Blake thank you so much for the 5 star review. We look forwarding to welcoming you into our community and appreciate your feedback.

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text:
I am not one to write google reviews, but I have had such a poor experience moving in to the Standard that it must be done. Ignore the near perfect rating -- the building ran a promotion encouraging people to write 5 star reviews before move in.

My apartment has not had AC for the first two weeks and the windows do not open. There is no organization for packages and mail. The bluetooth locking app often crashes and I cannot access the building or my apartment as there is no physical key. The building has been woefully unprepared for move in and there seems to be no end in sight.

The included cable did help when YouTube TV crashed mid-Celtics Heat Game 1. Still a trash place to live.
owner_answer: We are sorry to hear you have had a less than satisfactory experiance.  Please reach out to our leasing office to discuss.

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text:
First of all you should ignore all of the generic good reviews. The Standard ran a promotion with the residents for some raffle give away if you left a five star review in the Spring before anyone moved in.

This is not a shot at the staff, they are trying, but the building is a mess. The only thing the Standard is good at is making sure they are charging us for rent and other fees.

This includes that they are literally charging 12 months rent for 11 months because they have "housing contracts" and not monthly rent. I've never heard of anything like this in my life. They blatantly misled me into believing my monthly rent would be much lower than it is.

The place is a mess and a complete ripoff, if you are considering other options I would go with them.
owner_answer: We are sorry to hear you have had a less than satisfactory experiance. Please reach out to our leasing office to discuss.

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text:
I have never had such a bad experience with this apartment! If you are going to stay in this apartment, I suggest you run as far away as possible! The rooms have no ventilation fans and no windows! The air conditioner and dishwasher are always broken! And the air conditioner and washing machine are as loud as an airplane engine. Also, their garbage room is almost never cleaned and the garbage fills up and overflows in the hallway.
And the most important one is: the attitude of their leasing office people is extremely rude and mean. they don't have the slightest service staff's attitude and feel superior. They will treat you like a slave and you can't defend your legal rights because of the mandatory contract.
All in all, this is the worst apartment in the entire United States, bar none!
owner_answer: Xyancheng,  we are sorry you have had a less than satisfactory experiance.  We are happy to discuss any concerns you have, please be sure to reach out to us direclty at the Leasing Office.

review_text: Joshua is helpful and friendly - the best at tours. I didn’t feel rushed through the tour and I felt he answered all of my questions honestly.

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text: Beware, they've solicited good reviews for "points" before anyone has moved in. The reality: premium price for the an obviously unprepared building and staff. AC hasn't worked in two weeks. Move in was a two hour wait. Mail room is entirely unsorted and impossible to find packages. When the staff is asked? They have no idea what's going on and are overwhelmed.

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text: Windows don't open. Flooding and water damage. Messy commons areas. And none of the amenities are open. The gym has been closed for 2 weeks and the student office area had to paper so I could not print. This apartment does one thing proper ; offer empty promises. For the price point this place should be arrested for theft.

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text:
I would like to know why the standard chooses to employ a bonfire for a heating system????? WHY does my room smell like burning plastic when I turn the heat on, and on top of that, even worse, WHY does the fire alarm go off when I turn on the heat???? Why does the standard leave the residents two options, freeze in their own unit, or be victim to a prospective gas fire. Its a brand new building, ridiculous. And wheres the Tesla?? Why am I paying for this
A sad excuse for a living unit. How can I live comfortably when my unit is about to catch on fire when I turn on the heat, or I cannot even wash my dishes or clothes because the washing machine and dishwasher are broken. And IF THEY DO WORK I feel like I joined the ROTC airforce academy program because they sound like fighter jets taking off for war..... IN A BRAND NEW APARTMENT??? They give us broken, junk appliances? Be for real, careful what you choose to lease
If you wish to take a shower, I would suggest using an outdoor garden hose before I suggested taking a shower at the standard. There is legit no pressure in my shower and the water that does trickle out is freezing. I quite literally would rather be hit with 20 water balloons than shower at the standard. The water would be warmer. Im not sure if they are trying to prepare us for war and cut off the hot water supply, but I didnt sign up for this
owner_answer: We appreciate your feedback. Please feel free to contact the leasing office directly for any problems you are experiencing, we would be happy to assist you.

name: The Standard at Ann Arbor
review_text: I was happy to live at this place at first before I moved in but now it’s an embarrassment. It’s a shame that this place is a ripoff! If you plan on living here don’t do it. I’m paying $1460 a month for a one bedroom (divided) with a shared bathroom. They’ve lied about the retail stores that the construction workers were supposed to have built before the apartment was available for move in. The packages are always scattered all over the place and trash is piled up right by the 1st floor of the building by the side entrance. Do not live here they are scammers and will rip you off!
owner_answer:
Hey Jomo, we are sorry to see you are so disappointed. Our retail space has been completed since move in, it has been awaiting a tenant to move in. Since our Luxer packing room has been operational we have not been made aware of any large amounts of packages that have been left unattended for an extended period of time. Please let the leasing office know if you are still experiencing any of these inconveniences and we would be more than happy to assist you in finding a solution.

-The Standard Team

review_text: Just go to the leasing office and ask them about the Tesla, or check out the lower level retail!  The tesla isn't here, and the lower level retail isn't finished.  You'll have incorrect balances due, cold showers, and problems with the inspection you need to complete.  You also don't get a key, which means if your phone dies, and you're not in your apartment, you're not getting in.  All of the positive reviews are from before the building opened, and it's sad, because I know a lot of people (including myself) were really excited about this, especially since it's obviously not cheap.
